"{\"uid\": \"thegatewaypundit.com-2024-08-gold-medalist-turns-olympic-news-conference-worship-concert\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"At its core, professing the Christian faith means believing with all our heart that God brings light out of darkness.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 28, \"end\": 37, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_music\", \"score\": 0.599451343333496, \"rank\": 0.6575016977437309, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_music\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thus, it should not surprise us when we see it happen, but it still has the power to amaze.\", \"from\": 119, \"to\": 210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At a press conference on Friday at thewokeandblasphemousOlympics in Paris, gold medalist Yemisi Ogunleye of Germany responded to a moderator's question by breaking into a gospel song in praise of Jesus.\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 280, \"end\": 285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999507226688, \"rank\": 4.9277196606631644e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 320, \"end\": 327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.955644440245735, \"rank\": 0.040513447740287874, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.982827814702726, \"rank\": 0.017472221501379614, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To his credit, the moderator prompted Ogunleye with a question seemingly designed to call forth a worshipful hymn.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yemi, is it true you sing in the gospel choir?\\\"\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemi_A.D.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yemi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemi_A.D.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yemi_A.D.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"he asked.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When she replied in the affirmative, he asked her what song she had going through her head during the competition.\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According toAthletics Weekly, Ogunleye won the women's shot put gold medal in dramatic fashion.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After entering the final round in second place, she saved her best throw for last, earning a come-from-behind victory over Maddison-Lee Wesche of New Zealand.\", \"from\": 804, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Wesch\\u00e9\", \"score\": 0.669467902590356, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wesche\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Wesch\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Walter_Wesch\\u00e9\"}, {\"begin\": 950, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\", \"score\": 0.9841240095836753, \"rank\": 0.013950496057435233, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealanders\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just lifted my hands and prayed before my final attempt, and I wanted to have a good last round,\\\" Ogunleye said.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1079, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Then after that throw and realizing it would maybe be good enough for gold, I thought, 'Thank you, Jesus.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The newly-minted gold medalist brought that same spirit of gratitude to her press-conference rendition of \\\"I Almost Let Go.\\\"\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Writtenmore than 20 years agoby Grammy Award-nominated gospel composerKurt Carr, \\\"I Almost Let Go\\\" tells a story of a person who nearly succumbed to depression before experiencingGod'ssalvation.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\", \"score\": 0.999999987321644, \"rank\": 1.2127571811813245e-08, \"text\": \"Grammy\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grammy_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ogunleye sang eleven lines from the middle of the song:  I almost let go.I was quite at the edge of a breakthrough,But could not see it.The devil really had me,But Jesus came and grabbed me.He held me close, so I would not let go.God's mercy kept me, so I would not let go.So I am here today because God kept me.I am alive today only because of His grace.Oh, He kept me.\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1676, \"end\": 1681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.982827814702726, \"rank\": 0.017472221501379614, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus_in_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"God kept me.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"God's mercies kept me,So I would not let go.\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The German gold medalist's powerful and angelic voice belted out those lyrics for 52 seconds.\", \"from\": 1942, \"to\": 2035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9990808487986337, \"rank\": 0.0009077208322536256, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was the song that I was just singing,\\\" she then said as the moderator, silver-medalistWescheand bronze-medalistJiayuan Songof China applauded the performance.\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2169, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9742997023951677, \"rank\": 0.02520695331982923, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Readers may watch the press conference below.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ogunleye began singing at the 9:30 mark.\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With her rendition of \\\"I Almost Let Go,\\\" Ogunleye became the latest female athlete to redeem thediabolical Olympics.\", \"from\": 2293, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, in an interview with NBC's Mike Tirico, American hurdler and gold-medalistSydney McLaughlin-Levronegave glory to God.\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2446, \"end\": 2449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999996150750862, \"rank\": 2.8906156537795514e-07, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\